<hl>
<seg id=1> Cuanglupei said that: Thailand will hold a general election ahead of time. </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> (Bangkok) The night before last night, the Thai Prime Minister, Cuanglupei, said that, he is going to have a general election ahead of the expiration of the Seven Parties Combined Government in October, 2000. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> However, he added that, now that the Combined Government is in a steady state, it is capable of carrying out the economic reform program. </seg>
<seg id=4> He said that, this kind of economic reform holds in the balance the ability to resuscitate the economy and maintain the economic growth. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> While giving his speech at a dinner party held by the Thailand Overseas Reporters' Club, Cuanglupei said that, "The foreign investors' confidence is closely bound up with a steady government and the persistence of the policies, which we will always keep in mind." </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> "We do not plan to wait for our expiration of term. </seg>
<seg id=7> We will dedicate the use of the time that we still have at hand to fulfill our country's economic reform, and make a firm and steady foundation for steady development in the future." </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> Cuanglupei said that it is not decided when the Congress will be dismissed and the election will be held. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=9> Thailand has not yet broken away from its crisis. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=10> In addition, while giving his speech, Cuanglupei also advised that Thailand has not yet broken away from its crisis. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=11> He pointed out that, the current condition is still "frail", the global elements may induce Thailand to wander off the goal, which is to turn around the economy during the second half of 1999. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=12> However, he pledged that he will carry through the extensive reform measures, and put an end to corruption, which has weakened this country's economy. </seg>
</p>
